article.headline: Murray State 58, Rider 51
article.story: LAWRENCEVILLE, N.J. (AP) -- Danero Thomas scored six of his game-high 19 points in the closing minutes to lead Murray State to a 58-51 win over Rider on Saturday night. Tyler Holloway added 10 points and Marvin Williams had nine points and eight rebounds for the Racers (14-13), who won despite making just 38.6 percent of their shots. Jason Thompson had 14 points and 12 rebounds for the Broncs (14-13), but also committed six turnovers before fouling out. Ryan Thompson added 12 points and nine rebounds for Rider, while Harris Mansell added eight points and eight rebounds. The Broncs seemed prime for a comeback win when they went on a 10-4 run to tie the game at 49-49 with 3:05 to play. Thomas, though, then hit a 3-pointer and made three free throws while the Racers held Rider to just two points down the stretch. Overall, the Broncs shot just 27.8 percent from the floor and were 3-of-21 from 3-point range.
